data.title: Curbside service!!
data.text: The Curbside service that Applebee's offers make life easier with Having a newborn. I make my reservations online or by phone and they meet me at my car. They never have me waiting more than a few minutes. Awesome service.

data.title: Superb service
data.text: Wow, I didn't come here expecting to say wow! From the moment we entered until we left the service was warm, friendly, efficient, and perfect. The food wasn't bad either. 2 for $20 includes two meals and an appetizer...bargain! Electronic menu/gaming on the tables if you want to order/pay/play sans human interaction. Menifee is the town of chain restaurants and another dozen are just opening. So, if you're on the fence about which chain to try, this place is WAY above standards for this chain and well above standards for most chains. Thanks, Zach, and thank you to the team for a delightful dinner.

data.title: Excellent menu, comfortable atmosphere, excellent food.
data.text: I went here for a Father's Day celebration -- but on a weekday.  The menu at Applebee's has been greatly expanded from what it was several years ago, and the dish I had was well prepared--a shrimp salad. The servers were friendly and efficient. The dessert (a mud pie a la mode) was very good -- and quite large enough to split between me and my daughter.

data.title: A decent place to eat at good prices!
data.text: Even thought Appleby's is a chain, this particular restaurant is well run, cares about the customers and gives good service and has good prices. It is located just West of the 215 freeway at the Newport road exit in Menifee. There were four of us having a late lunch today, and the servers were friendly and attentive, the bar drinks were decent for the price and the food was plentiful and served hot, a plus in my book. I would eat here again when I am in the area.

data.title: Just ok
data.text: I had the soup and salad.  French onion soup was pretty good, but the salad well lets say it was all dressing with a little salad.  Grand daughter wasn't really happy with the cheese bread pizza. I was really surprised she didn't care for the cheese sticks either.  She usually loves them at BJ's  Waitress was very nice.

data.title: Not bad for a chain restaurant
data.text:
Was just at Applebee's recently  I have to say when I first went there years ago, the food was mediocre.  Today, it's pretty darn good.  The salads are really tasty, they have an ahi tuna that is really good, sushi grade.  They have specialty iced tea drinks.  My favorite is the black cherry with honey.  Yummy.  

During the week they have lunch specials and the prices are very reasonable.  

I never though I would say this but give Applebee's a try.  They've changed.

data.title: Customer Service was outstanding
data.text: The food was good, but the customer service from my server (Mike) was outstanding! I would recommend waiting for his area if you want great, friendly, service.

data.title: Could have been a five circle rating.
data.text: Easy to find and easy to access for all, we were greeted warmly and shown to our table, a booth by a window.  Our server, Joel was superb, engaging in conversation with great humour. We ordered the chicken and shrimp skillet with a side salad. Everything was delivered promptly and presented well. The salad was fresh, I had it with an excellent ranch dressing, the chicken skillet piping hot and very tasty. All so far made me think that with the excellent pricing this was heading for a five circle rating, then I went to the restroom.  What a shame, these were terrible, due only to their lack of attention. Below the male wall urinal, the floor was wet, the surfaces around the sink were wet, paper towels on the floor and the waste bin full. I'm glad I went after my meal, what a shame.

data.title: Not really impressed!
data.text: I wasn't there during a busy time so I was surprised how slow the service was.....I know how hard it is to work in the food service industry,  so I try to give them the benefit of the doubt...I did try something new they had on the menu, something enchilada, it was cold and the flavor just didn't do it for me.....so it could have been a off day for them, several people called in sick who knows, but I just don't think I will go back.

data.title: Nice atmosphere
data.text:
For a chain restaurant, the Appleby's in Menifee is a nice gathering place for friends and family. The staff is friendly, a big plus in my opinion. The menu is ok, typical for this type of restaurant. I've had lunch there several times, and so far I've had satisfactory meals. 
Overall, I'd say it's a good neighborhood restaurant conveniently located near Menifee's growing shopping area.

data.title: Ribs
data.text: We visited this restaurant for the first time. The ribs were not good, not smoked and doesn't fall of the bone. So for real good ribs, we will go next time somewhere else.

data.title: New and effieient
data.text: Great food and value. New Restaurant and very east to get to. Their location is perfect. As good as any Applebee's I've eaten at.

data.title: Dinner
data.text: The table was not cleaned and set up and ready for us,We had to send the Steak back twice before it was cooked to the order the Manager did apologize,the rest of the meal was sub par. Not the best dinner experience,If we ever go back I would not order the sirloin steak.

data.title: Great Food & Service (except for the sirloin steak - not good)
data.text:
We eat at this Applebees at least once a week.  I especially like their Oriental Chicken Salad and the items on the Have It All menu that are under 600 calories.  Our servers are usually very friendly and attentive and make sure are drinks are refilled when needed.  (Michael is great!)
I would have rated this restaurant 5 stars; however, there is a problem with Applebees’ sirloin steak.  It is absolutely the worst piece of meat we have tasted.  I tried it only once, but my husband has tried it four times now, always with the same result.  This steak is so tough that you cannot chew it enough to swallow it!  Tonight, he finally said “enough” and sent it back with the Manager and ordered something else.  
I wouldn’t be writing about this if it was just a one-time thing, but it's not.  We are very surprised that a restaurant like Applebees would serve a steak that is so bad.  If the company executives or chefs would actually try eating it, they would know instantly what we're talking about.  
On a side note.....I know all the restaurants are going to the table kiosk for payment.  However, some of us prefer personal, face-to-face contact rather than machines.  If we don't want to use the machine, we should not be forced to do so.  Applebees' policy (at least in Menifee) is that you have no choice, YOU MUST PAY BY MACHINE.  This isn't right.  If I don't want to use the kiosk, I shouldn't have to.  This is very poor customer service on Applebees' part (not the server's!).

data.title: Good Place to Eat in Menifee
data.text: The menu is varied which helps for my family as we have allergies and some prefer low calorie entrees.  The wait staff is always willing to get information on nut allergies for my daughter.  My family has eaten many times at this restaurant and the food is always consistently good.

data.title: It is a place to return to.
data.text: This Applebee's chain is very new and is very busy.  The food is good and deserves to be a great choice for lunch and/or dinner.

data.title: SECRETS TO abz
data.text: MORE SECRETS... 1st about servers, top 3 tall-Beth, handlebar mustache Robbie and rockn Tiffanie ,  youll see them all walking fast and anything you ask for its there BAM!   they make me feel like Im   "Mr Apple"...  on to food,  again my fav is  2 for $25, adding minced garlic to the spinach dip, yum,   bourbon shrimp n chix WITH lemon cream sauce again garlic, the sauce carmelizes when it hits the sizzling iron platter, every bite is smoking hot , next time I will see if they have a balsamic dressing which smells amassing sizzling.  my wife  went super duper healthy  instead of potatoes she got lots of zucchini n mushrooms.     they love doing these things make sure  you over-tip

data.title: Understaffed
data.text: The food and selection was good just understaffed when I was there for my birthday.  The server was very nice and efficient but the soda was flat and tasteless; we had to return it.

data.title: Great Place for Lunch
data.text:
Love to eat at the bar.  It would be even better if they would seat familys with children (of any age) in one of the main dining room seating areas.  Great drinks, good price for what you get.
Also recommend they get all their staff to start keeping things cleaner.  Everytime we go there is something sticky or wet.

data.title: Good food great service
data.text: We have gone here many times and have always had great service.  The prices are starting to be on the high side but so are the rest of the places.
